{"title_page": "Nana Ama Agyemang Asante", "text_new": "{{Orphan|date=April 2020}}\n{{short description|Ghanaian Journalist}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Nana Ama Agyemang Asante\n| image              = \n| imagesize          = \n| alt                = \n| caption            = \n| birth_date         = \n| birth_place        = \n| othername          = \n| occupation         = Journalist & Writer\n| yearsactive        = \n| website            = \n}}\n\n'''Nana Ama Agyemang Asante''' is a Ghanaian journalist, editor and writer.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://citinewsroom.com/author/nana-ama/|title=Nana Ama Agyemang Asante|last=|first=|date=|website=citinewsroom.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=15 February 2020}}</ref> From 2012 up to the present day she has been working as deputy online editor of [[Citi FM (Ghana)|Citi FM]]'s web portal [http://citifmonline.com/ citifmonline.com]. She also co-hosts the \u201cCiti Breakfast Show\u201d at the Accra-based radio station [[Citi FM (Ghana)|Citi FM]], together with [[Bernard Avle]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://citifmonline.com/2017/10/citi-fms-nana-ama-agyemang-asante-attends-reagan-fascell-democracy-fellowship/|title=Citi FM\u2019s Nana Ama Agyemang Asante attends Reagan-Fascell Democracy Fellowship program in US|last=citifmonline.com|first=|date=16 October 2017|website=citifmonline.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=28 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Education ==\nShe completed her tertiary education at the University of Cape Coast where she studied Sociology and Economics.[''citation needed'']\n\n== Career ==\nNana Ama Agyemang Asante started her journalistic career in 2006 as a broadcast journalist with the radio station [[Joy FM (Ghana)|Joy FM]]. From 2011 to 2012 she worked with [[Journalists for Human Rights]] (JHR), an NGO which was founded in Canada, where she served as the country director for Ghana.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sheleadsafrica.org/nana-ama-agyemang-asante/|title=Nana Ama Agyemang Asante: Women Journalists Endure Misogeny, Sexism and General Disrespect in Their Line of Duty|last=Kwenu Smith|first=Emma|date=|website=She.Leads.Africa|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=15 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe radio program \u201cCiti Breakfast Show\u201d (#CitiCBS), in which Nana Ama Agyemang Asante regularly participates, was awarded with a number of prizes over the years.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.modernghana.com/news/725589/citi-breakfast-show-named-cimg-radio-programme.html|title=Citi Breakfast Show named CIMG radio programme of the year|last=Allotey|first=Godwin A.|last2=Kwakofi|first2=Edwin|date=9 October 2016|website=Modern Ghana|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=28 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.primenewsghana.com/general-news/23rd-gja-awards-full-list-of-winners.html|title=23rd GJA Awards: Full list of winners|last=Yakubu|first=Mutala|date=28 October 2018|website=Prime News Ghana|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=28 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nM24, an African entertainment network, named Nana Ama Agyemang Asante \u201cRadio Personality of the Year\u201d in 2015 for her persistent efforts in speaking truth to power.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://democracychronicles.org/evaluation-of-ghanas-democracy/|title=VIDEO: An Evaluation Of Ghana\u2019s Democracy|last=DC Editors|first=|date=20 January 2018|website=Democracy Chronicles|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=28 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, she was awarded a \u201cReagan-Fascell Democracy Fellowship\u201d by the [[National Endowment for Democracy]] (NED), which allowed her to spend several months in Washington DC, USA to compile a report on the possibilities of the media to louden Ghanaian women's voices in the public sphere.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://reutersinstitute.politics.ox.ac.uk/people/nana-ama-agyemang-asante|title=Nana Ama Agyemang Asante|last=|first=|date=n.d.|website=Reuters Institute|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=28 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n\n<references />\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Ghanaian journalists]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Ghanaian writers]]\n[[Category:Ghanaian women activists]]\n", "text_old": "{{Orphan|date=April 2020}}\n{{short description|Ghanaian Journalist}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Nana Ama Agyemang Asante\n| image              = \n| imagesize          = \n| alt                = \n| caption            = \n| birth_date         = \n| birth_place        = \n| othername          = \n| occupation         = Journalist\n| yearsactive        = \n| website            = \n}}\n\n'''Nana Ama Agyemang Asante''' is a Ghanaian journalist, editor and writer.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://citinewsroom.com/author/nana-ama/|title=Nana Ama Agyemang Asante|last=|first=|date=|website=citinewsroom.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=15 February 2020}}</ref> From 2012 up to the present day she has been working as deputy online editor of [[Citi FM (Ghana)|Citi FM]]'s web portal [http://citifmonline.com/ citifmonline.com]. She also co-hosts the \u201cCiti Breakfast Show\u201d at the Accra-based radio station [[Citi FM (Ghana)|Citi FM]], together with [[Bernard Avle]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://citifmonline.com/2017/10/citi-fms-nana-ama-agyemang-asante-attends-reagan-fascell-democracy-fellowship/|title=Citi FM\u2019s Nana Ama Agyemang Asante attends Reagan-Fascell Democracy Fellowship program in US|last=citifmonline.com|first=|date=16 October 2017|website=citifmonline.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=28 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Education ==\nShe completed her tertiary education at the University of Cape Coast where she studied Sociology and Economics.[''citation needed'']\n\n== Career ==\nNana Ama Agyemang Asante started her journalistic career in 